At 08:54 PM 9/10/01 -0500, al brase wrote:
>Paul:
>Could be one of three things:
>1. Generator - regulator problems
>2. Battery no good
>3. A parasitic load, i.e., something draining the battery while the engine
is not
>running.
>I'd check for this (3.)

And to check, disconnect the negative cable from the battery and connect an
ammeter between the two. If there is current flowing, you have a drain. (If
you have clock, there will be a tiny flow. If so, disconnectt the clock
before you try this.)
Ian Cameron

